<span class="displaytext">hillary vows to take on the special interests and be a partner for working families in two new ads airing in kentucky today. <p>with families living paycheck to paycheck, hillary vows to stand up for the middle class and provide solutions to our toughest challenges in the 30-second spot, entitled "partner." </p><p>watch "partner" here. </p><p>in the second 30-second spot, entitled "right track," hillary promises to close corporate tax loopholes and put america back on the right track. </p><p>watch "right track" here. </p><p>following is the script for "partner." </p><p>"partner"<br/> tv :30 </p><p>(candidate full): we're going to roll up our sleeves and provide the solutions that america desperately needs. </p><p>woman 1: we're living paycheck to paycheck. </p><p>man 1: it's hard to decide between a gallon of milk and a gallon of gas. </p><p>(candidate full): it's time that the american worker had a partner in the whitehouse. </p><p>man 2: (candidate full) can turn this country around. </p><p>woman 2: hillary has what it takes. </p><p>(candidate full): the wealthy and the well connected have had a president,<br/> it's time the middle class had a president who will stand up for you. </p><p>woman 3: she will put up a very strong fight for people like me. </p><p>(candidate full): i'm (candidate full) and i approved this message. *** </p><p>following is the script for "right track." </p><p>"right track"<br/> tv :30 </p><p>(candidate full): it is wrong that a wall street money manager making fifty million dollars a year pays a lower percentage of his income in taxes than a nurse or a teacher or a truck driver or an auto worker making fifty thousand dollars. </p><p>anncr: (candidate full) will end loopholes for special interests and cut taxes for working families to pay for college, healthcare and retirement. it's time for action. </p><p>(candidate full): we will put america back on the right track. </p><p>i'm (candidate full) and i approved this message.</p></span>



